# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 
    ==> Quick view:  for some of these critical web services the only form of protection is being hidden from the general public, 
    exchanging critical information without or very few protection. WSDL Disclosure attacks aim at discovering non-public web services 
    by retrieving their WSDL file.



    ==> Methods:
        - Google Dork.
        - Spidering.
        - appending ?wsdl at the end of URL.
        - directory/files Bruteforce.
# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 